[143.394675, "o", "232;220;198m1. \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198mToken/CEL mechanism: Celsius paid interest partly in its proprietary CEL token and actively bought back CEL on the open market, creating circular token-price risk; the pitch does no\r\n\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m  \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;185;192;171m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m    \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198mt mention a native token. 2. Scale and geography: Celsius operated globally with $12B AUM and 1.7M customers; the pitch is US-only and early-stage ('M' of assets). 3. Rehypothecation d\r\n\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m  \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;185;192;171m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m    \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198mepth: Celsius was documented to have 'endlessly re-hypothecated assets вЂ¦\u001b[9;79H lending the same assets over and over,' which the pitch does not describe. 4. Revenue diversification: Celsius \r\n\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m  \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;185;192;171m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m    \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198malso ear"]
